  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">Wandsworth Council continues to take the lead in <a href="/hashtag/London?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>London</b></a> when it comes to making it easier for residents to go electric<a href="https://t.co/xy0lVf6sYf" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/wandbc/status/974686811166560256" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/wandbc/status/974686811166560256"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/wandbc/status/</span><span class="invisible">974686811166560256</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>
</div>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">"Having that pit of fear in the beginning is not a bad thing.   <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="0">1,198 new homes <img class="Emoji Emoji--forText" src="https://abs.twimg.com/emoji/v2/72x72/1f3e0.png" draggable="false" alt="" title="House building" aria-label="Emoji: House building" /> <img class="Emoji Emoji--forText" src="https://abs.twimg.com/emoji/v2/72x72/1f3e1.png" draggable="false" alt="" title="House with garden" aria-label="Emoji: House with garden" /> and a 29m contribution to local infrastructure approved last night at planning committee, in 3 schemes with leading affordable housing figures of 53%, 37%, 35%. Conservative <a href="/wandsworth" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="15011317"><s>@</s><b>wandsworth</b></a> producing some of best housing figures in London month after month.</p>

  <p class="TweetTextSize TweetTextSize--normal js-tweet-text tweet-text" lang="en" data-aria-label-part="4">Over 200 residents in the door already. <a href="/hashtag/ConstructWandsworth?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>ConstructWandsworth</b></a> proving a great success for the second year running. <a href="/hashtag/WorkMatch?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>WorkMatch</b></a> <a href="/wandbc" class="twitter-atreply pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr" data-mentioned-user-id="18020011"><s>@</s><b>wandbc</b></a> creating <a href="/hashtag/ConstructionJobs?src=hash" data-query-source="hashtag_click" class="twitter-hashtag pretty-link js-nav" dir="ltr"><s>#</s><b>ConstructionJobs</b></a> borough wide.<a href="https://t.co/41L1NdThbb" rel="nofollow noopener" dir="ltr" data-expanded-url="https://twitter.com/kimcaddy/status/956540708571287552" class="twitter-timeline-link u-hidden" target="_blank" title="https://twitter.com/kimcaddy/status/956540708571287552"><span class="tco-ellipsis"></span><span class="invisible">https://</span><span class="js-display-url">twitter.com/kimcaddy/statu</span><span class="invisible">s/956540708571287552</span><span class="tco-ellipsis"><span class="invisible"></span></span></a></p>
